```class Solution {
public:
    int minInsertions(string s) {
        int res = 0, left = 0;
        for (char c : s) {
            if (c == '(') left++;
            else if (left > 0) left--;
            else res++;
        }
        return res + left * 2;
    }
};```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: We iterate through the string once, keeping track of the number of open parentheses and the number of insertions needed. We increment the insertions whenever we encounter a closing parenthesis without a matching open parenthesis. At the end, we add the number of unmatched open parentheses multiplied by 2 (since each one needs two closing parentheses).

